==English==

===Etymology===
The name ''Cú Roí'' probably means "hound of the battlefield."

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''[[Cú]] [[Roí]] ([[mac]] [[Dáire]])'''

# {{cattag|Irish mythology}} A king of [[Munster]] and a [[sorcerer]] who can [[transform]] at will. He was killed by [[Cúchulainn]], but his death was avenged by his son [[Lugaid mac Con Roí]], who was subsequently killed by [[Conall the Victorious]].

